<paragraph id="E35B9301FFD6AC74F15E270DFB8AFD10" blockId="5.[340,1248,562,643]" pageId="5">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Large species, 
<quantity id="241C3EE4FFD6AC74F2C5270CFC98FDDB" box="[719,796,562,584]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="5" unit="mm" value="3.9">3.9 mm</quantity>
(abdomen fully extended). Coloration: head blackish; pronotum and elytra reddish brown; abdomen blackish, with the apex and segments 
<collectionCode id="85F50BC4FFD6AC74F1B22750FE70FD10" box="[440,500,622,643]" pageId="5">III-IV</collectionCode>
slightly paler; legs testaceous; antennae dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFD6AC74F15E27ACFCD2FD70" blockId="5.[340,1248,658,739]" pageId="5">
Facies as in 
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFD6AC74F1D227ACFDA1FD3B" box="[472,549,658,680]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
. Head and pronotum with shallow fine microreticulation (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFD6AC74F48F27ACFB57FD3B" box="[1157,1235,658,680]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Eyes moderately small, weakly protruding from lateral outline of head, slightly less than half the length of postocular region in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
<caption id="B79BC389FFD6AC74F15E2360FB64F9E1" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5434900" box="[340,1248,1630,1650]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="5" startId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" targetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFD6AC74F15E2360FB64F9E1" blockId="5.[340,1248,1630,1718]" box="[340,1248,1630,1650]" pageId="5">
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD6AC74F15E2360FE33F9E1" bold="true" box="[340,439,1630,1650]" pageId="5">Figs 13-19</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="24E4E882FFD6AC74F1CE2360FDD7F9E1" authority="Homson, 1974" authorityName="Homson" authorityYear="1974" box="[452,595,1630,1650]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anlasi" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD6AC74F1CE2360FDD7F9E1" box="[452,595,1630,1650]" italics="true" pageId="5">Geostiba anlasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CAA3F268FFD6AC74F2532360FD01F9E1" box="[601,645,1630,1650]" pageId="5" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(holotype): (
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD6AC74F2F72360FC90F9E1" bold="true" box="[765,788,1630,1650]" pageId="5">13</emphasis>
) habitus; (
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD6AC74F3852360FC22F9E1" bold="true" box="[911,934,1630,1650]" pageId="5">14</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD6AC74F4382360FBCDF9E1" bold="true" box="[1074,1097,1630,1650]" pageId="5">15</emphasis>
) anterior part of
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFD6AC74F17A234BFE47F925" blockId="5.[340,1248,1630,1718]" pageId="5">
abdomen; (
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD6AC74F1D3234BFE74F91A" bold="true" box="[473,496,1653,1673]" pageId="5">16</emphasis>
) right elytron in lateral view; (
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD6AC74F33E234BFCCFF91A" bold="true" box="[820,843,1653,1673]" pageId="5">17</emphasis>
) tergite VIII; (
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD6AC74F3FC234BFB89F91A" bold="true" box="[1014,1037,1653,1673]" pageId="5">18</emphasis>
) sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="D1904F13FFD6AC74F4CB234BFB5CF91A" bold="true" box="[1217,1240,1653,1673]" pageId="5">19</emphasis>
) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 13: 1.0 mm; 14-15: 
<quantity id="241C3EE4FFD6AC74F3F123B2FBC1F933" box="[1019,1093,1676,1696]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
; 16-18: 
<quantity id="241C3EE4FFD6AC74F49823B2FB58F933" box="[1170,1244,1676,1696]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
; 19: 
<quantity id="241C3EE4FFD6AC74F17D239CFE3BF925" box="[375,447,1698,1718]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFD6AC74F15E23FBFB4AF886" blockId="5.[340,1248,1733,1813]" pageId="5">
Pronotum apparently without appreciable sexual dimorphism, distinctly convex in crosssection, approximately 1.15 times as wide as head and 1.05 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFD6AC74F48023DCFB50F96B" box="[1162,1236,1762,1784]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="5">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Elytra with pronounced sexual dimorphism, approximately 0.55 times as long as pronotum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFD5AC77F308245BFCB6FEE9" blockId="6.[770,818,357,378]" box="[770,818,357,378]" pageId="6">1185</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFD5AC77F15E2491FCB7FDCB" blockId="6.[340,1248,431,600]" pageId="6">
Abdomen rather shining; puncturation relatively sparse and fine on anterior tergites, very sparse and very fine on posterior tergites; microsculpture on tergites VI-VII very shallow, barely noticeable, on tergites III-V obsolete; segment III conspicuously elongated, ratio of width (across posterior margin) and length (from anterior margin of paratergite to posterior margin of tergite): 1.23 (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFD5AC77F2C9271BFC97FDA8" box="[707,787,549,571]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of tergite 
<collectionCode id="85F50BC4FFD5AC77F447271BFBF4FDA9" box="[1101,1136,549,570]" pageId="6">VII</collectionCode>
with very indistinct narrow rudiment of a palisade fringe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E35B9301FFD5AC77F1632757FE3DFCBC" blockId="6.[340,1248,616,815]" pageId="6">
: elytra with ill-defined, somewhat granulose puncturation (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFD5AC77F3E02756FBBFFDED" box="[1002,1083,616,638]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); laterally with pronounced (long and strongly elevated, especially posteriorly) fold (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFD5AC77F43327B8FB0EFD0F" box="[1081,1162,646,668]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); suture slightly elevated (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFD5AC77F203279DFDD1FD2A" box="[521,597,675,697]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); abdominal tergites III-V without tubercles; tergite 
<collectionCode id="85F50BC4FFD5AC77F463279AFB08FD2A" box="[1129,1164,676,697]" pageId="6">VII</collectionCode>
without process; tergite VIII highly distinctive: posterior margin with pair of pronounced processes (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFD5AC77F1A827E0FE6AFD67" box="[418,494,734,756]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); sternite VIII as in 
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFD5AC77F2B727E0FC8CFD67" box="[701,776,734,756]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
; median lobe of aedeagus with dagger-shaped cristal process (
<figureCitation id="7BDF8F84FFD5AC77F1F427C5FDCBFC82" box="[510,591,763,785]" captionStart="Figs 13-19" captionStartId="5.[340,380,1630,1650]" captionTargetBox="[341,1203,755,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-125@5.[340,1211,1152,1605]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 13-19: Geostiba anlasi sp.n. (holotype): (13) habitus; (14) forebody; (15) anterior part of" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434900/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
